Inevitable errors in the current investigation chiefly originate from the measurement of the PCM temperature and droplet impact velocity. The paraffin temperature prior to the impact was attained by a k-type thermocouple, whose accuracy was 0.5 °C. Furthermore, the temperature distribution of the PCM surface was determined by an IR camera having an accuracy of 0.3 °C. In addition, data post-processing was implemented with an accuracy of 1 pixel, which corresponds to a 0.11 mm error. Thus, given the shooting rate of the camera (1200 fps), the impact velocity was calculated with an accuracy of 0.13 m/s. Based on Taylor’s theory, the uncertainty in the Weber number is as follows46:5δWeWe=δDD2+2δvv2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
